Abstract :

This project is designed to help individuals, especially elderly patients, remember to take 
their medication on time. By using an IoT system with real-time alerts, it ensures that users 
receive timely reminders and confirmations. The system also sends notifications to 
caregivers if a dose is missed, promoting better medication adherence and overall health 
management. 



Introduction: 

For elderly people or patients with chronic conditions, forgetting to take medications can lead 
to serious health risks. This project aims to solve that problem by creating a simple, 
automated reminder system that alerts users when it’s time to take their medicine. It also 
keeps caregivers informed by sending notifications if a dose is missed.



Objective: 

Provide timely reminders for medication. 
Confirm whether the user has taken the medicine. 
Notify caregivers if a dose is missed. 
Display the next scheduled dose on an OLED screen. 



Methodology: 

The system will be controlled by an ESP32 microcontroller. At scheduled times, a buzzer will 
sound, and an LED will blink to remind the user to take their medicine. The user confirms 
they’ve taken the medicine by pressing a push-button. If no confirmation is received within a 
set time, the system will send an alert to the caregiver and activate a louder buzzer. The 
OLED display will show the next medication time.



Components Used: 

ESP32 Microcontroller 
LEDs 
Buzzer 
Push-Button 
OLED Display 



Conclusion: 

The IoT-Based Smart Medicine Reminder & Monitoring System provides an easy way for 
patients to remember their medication schedule, helping them stay on track. It also improves 
caregiving by notifying caregivers if a dose is missed. This project aims to enhance 
medication adherence, ultimately supporting better health management.
